ad_creative_body:
Thanksgiving is a time for family, good food & one more day of early voting.

So I figured this is a good time to showcase one of my favourite meals to cook when the fam gets together.

Punjabi Poutine! It’s like Punjabi & Quebec styles merging.

Happy Thanksgiving!

ad_creative_body:
This is Grassy Narrows, where the devastating impacts of mercury contamination have impacted 3 generations.
We can make sure every community has access to clean water. We just have to make it a priority.
funding_entity: Canada’s NDP / Le NPD du Canada

ad_creative_body:
We need to take a minute and seriously ask ourselves, why is it even a question whether Indigenous communities deserve clean drinking water or not?

It's a matter of priorities, and if I was Prime Minister, I'd get it done. #elxn43
ad_creative_link_title: This shouldn't even be a question

ad_creative_body:
You're paying some of the highest prices in the world for cell & internet service, while rich cell phone companies like Rogers and Bell make billions in profits every year and the Trudeau Liberals do nothing to fix this.

It doesn't have to be like this – the NDP has a plan to lower your cell phone bill and ensure better internet coverage for all Canadians.
ad_creative_link_description: High speed internet and cell services are a necessity for Canadians – and despite this, broadband access and wireless services are far from being affordable or reliable in Canada.

ad_creative_body: When rich corporations ask for tax breaks and handouts, the Trudeau Liberal government does whatever it takes to make it happen – yet federal workers can't even get a decent living wage. It shouldn't be like this. Our New Deal for People will implement a $15/hr federal min wage and help make life more affordable for workers and their families.
ad_creative_link_description: It’s time for Canada to reinstate a federal minimum wage for workers in federally-regulated workplaces and this time it should lead, not follow, provincial governments.
ad_creative_link_title: Canada should have a federal minimum wage | The Star
funding_entity: Canada’s NDP / Le NPD du Canada

ad_creative_body:
Once again, Prime Minister Trudeau is announcing another stall tactic to avoid pharmacare – a stall tactic that is yet another favour to the richest drug companies while millions of Canadians continue to skip the medicine they need or cut pills in half so a bottle lasts longer, because of the cost.

The NDP is leading the fight to expand medicare to include prescription drug coverage for everyone, regardless of their job status, where they live, their age, their health status, or how much money they make by implementing pharmacare for all: https://www.ndp.ca/pharmacare
ad_creative_link_description: Overhaul to Canadian system includes omitting U.S., Swiss plans from factoring into maximum prices and forcing drug makers to provide actual worth of medicine
ad_creative_link_title: Ottawa medicine board details changes to rules on national drug pricing
funding_entity: Canada’s NDP / Le NPD du Canada

ad_creative_body:
This is what happens when you have Liberal & Conservative governments in Ottawa giving ridiculous tax breaks to their wealthiest friends, while cutting back services people need. We need to stop catering to the ultra-rich & start putting everyday people first. 

My New Deal for People asks the multi-millionaires to pay just a little bit more, so that everyday families can have things like a Canadian prescription drug program. Let’s close the gap between the very richest and the rest of us: http://bit.ly/2YEG7km
ad_creative_link_description: Canada's wealthiest families are increasingly looking like dynasties.
ad_creative_link_title: Canada’s richest families own as much wealth as 3 provinces combined: report
